+## import mobile-share
+
+Imports files shared from a phone or sync folder into local memory records.
+
+Supported inputs:
+
+| Input | Behavior |
+|---|---|
+| folder | Recursively imports supported files |
+| `.zip` | Reads supported files inside the archive |
+| `.json` / `.html` / `.md` / `.txt` | Creates text memory records |
+| `.pdf` / images / Office files | Stores as attachments |
+
+```text
+python pala.py import mobile-share "C:\Users\you\Google Drive\ChatGPT Shares"
+```
+
+Useful options:
+
+| Option | Purpose |
+|---|---|
+| `--project trugurpala/pala-memory-core` | Link imported records to a project |
+| `--tag mobile` | Add an extra tag |
+| `--title "..."` | Override record title |
+| `--max-records 25` | Limit text records |
+| `--max-chars 12000` | Limit text stored per record |
+
 ## capture browser
 
 Captures a public or local URL into a memory record.
