+## Mobile Share Import Behavior
+
+The first mobile connector imports shared files from a local/synced folder or ZIP. It is designed for phone share sheets, Google Drive folders, iCloud/OneDrive sync folders, or manually copied files.
+
+| Input | Behavior |
+|---|---|
+| Text/Markdown/HTML/JSON | Creates local memory records |
+| PDF/images/Office files | Stores as attachments |
+| ZIP/folder | Processes supported files inside |
+
+Mobile background monitoring is intentionally deferred. The first reliable path is "share to folder, then import".
+
 ## Design Rule
 
 If a connector is fragile, keep it optional. The core should still work through manual capture and file import.
